<br>
But alot of people cannot handle the restrictions placed against new members of a guild or they cannot handle the commitment that a guild requires....but they also know that as soon as they change guilds they will have to go through the whole initiation process again, so they stick it out, with a negative feeling towards their current guild until they feel they have gotten everything they can from the guild...<br>
<br>
People like that, do indeed, suck.<br>
<br>
The better guilds out there will actually talk to people from your previous guild before considering you. If they find out you left the guild .00001 milliseconds after completing your epic, you won't get in. <br>
<br>
Pretty much all of the high level guilds are the same, with some variance in capability, but policy wise and how they treat their members is all comparably the same. <br>
<br>
In my eyes there are two main reasons where it is okay to change guilds. 1) Social relationships good or bad...you make new friends in another guild or you find that you and Member003 of your current guild just cannot get along at all. 2) The feeling that your current guild has ceased progressing in the game when there are other guilds out there getting better and still moving forward.<br>
<br>
You cannot argue with (1). and while (2) may appear slimey, when you look at it as that person is either going to quit the game out of boredom or move on...well move on is the better option for them.<br>
<br>
However as soon as you realize that you will be leaving a guild...leave. Don't drag it out, hoping for that last bit of loot or the help for your epic. That is simply rude and your negative feelings about a guild will hurt that guild and all of your social relationships in that guild. Save what you can of your reputation, your friends and get out as soon as you know you will be leaving. <br>
<br>
Some guilds will even help you finish your epic before you join them...both because they want to recruit people who dont loot and scoot and to test you to see if you do before they invest any serious loot with you.<br>
<br>
Some people just feel a need to move on if the current situation gets stale to them...Hopefully when they do, they will do so gracefully.<br>
